      <h2 id="styleguide-typography">Typography</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/base/typography.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/base/typography.css.scss</a>

      <p>All text is set in <strong>Lato</strong>. Some headings are set in uppercase <strong>Montserrat</strong>.</p>

      <p>The base font-size is 18px, with a line-height of 1.5.</p>

      <p>Links don't have a text-decoration: underline, but a border-bottom instead, with a slightly more transparent version of the color of the text (see color section).</p>

      <div class="example">
        <h1>Heading One</h1>
        <p>An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong>, <em>emphasized text</em> and <a href="#">a link</a>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.</p>

        <h2>Heading Two</h2>
        <p>An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong> and <em>emphasized text</em>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.</p>

        <h3>Heading Three</h3>
        <p>An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong> and <em>emphasized text</em>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.</p>

        <h4>Heading Four</h4>
        <p>An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong> and <em>emphasized text</em>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.</p>

        <h5>Heading Five</h5>
        <p>An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong> and <em>emphasized text</em>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.</p>

        <h6>Heading Six</h6>
        <p>
          An example paragraph with <strong>strong text</strong> and <em>emphasized text</em>, spanning multiple lines so you can see the line-height.
        </p>
      </div>


      <h2 id="styleguide-colors">Colors</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/base/colors.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/base/colors.css.scss</a>

      <p>
        Never use full black, instead opt for <code class="text-black">$black</code> or maybe even <code class="text-muted">$muted</code> gray. There is a <code class="text-primary">$primary</code> color for main actions. Other colors indicate the mood of the action such as <code class="text-success">$success</code>, <code class="text-warning">$warning</code> and <code class="text-danger">$danger</code>.
      </p>

      <p>Basic <a href="#">text links</a> use the <code>$primary</code> color.</p>

      <p>If you need a tinted version (like for drop shadows, see buttons section), use SCSS <code>darken($color, <strong>15%</strong>)</code>.</p>

      <div class="example">
        <ul class="color-swatch">
          <li class="bg-white text-black">White</li>
          <li class="bg-black text-white">Black</li>
          <li class="bg-primary text-white">Primary</li>
          <li class="bg-success text-white">Success</li>
          <li class="bg-warning text-white">Warning</li>
          <li class="bg-danger text-white">Danger</li>
          <li class="bg-muted">Muted</li>
        </ul>
      </div>


      <h2 id="styleguide-buttons">Buttons</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/modules/btn.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/modules/btn.css.scss</a>

      <p>All buttons have a disabled (opacity: .5) state, assigned with <code>disabled="disabled"</code></p>
      <p>Buttons get a little offset look with a 2px box-shadow on the y-axis in 15% darkened background-color.</p>

      <div class="example">
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Default button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default" disabled="disabled">Default disabled button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Primary button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-primary" disabled="disabled">Primary button disabled</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-success">Positive button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-success" disabled="disabled">Positive button disabled</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-warning">Warning button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-warning" disabled="disabled">Warning button disabled</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-danger">Danger button</a></p>
        <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-danger" disabled="disabled">Danger button disabled</a></p>
      </div>


      <h3>Button Groups</h3>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/modules/btn_group.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/modules/btn_group.css.scss</a>

      <p>Logically grouped buttons. Usually used when a user can take an exclusive action.</p>

      <div class="example">
        <div class="btn-group">
          <div class="btn">Example</div>
          <div class="btn">Example</div>
          <div class="btn">Example</div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <h2 id="styleguide-forms">Forms</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/modules/form.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/modules/form.css.scss</a>


      <div class="example">

        <form class="form" role="form">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="text1" class="form-label">Label</label>
            <input type="text" class="form-control" id="text1" placeholder="Placeholder" />
          </div>

          <div class="form-group" data-form-valid>
            <label for="text2" class="form-label">Label for valid input</label>
            <input type="text" class="form-control"  id="text2" placeholder="Placeholder" />
          </div>

          <div class="form-group" data-form-danger>
            <label for="text3" class="form-label">Label <span>for invalid input</span></label>
            <input type="text" class="form-control" id="text3" placeholder="Placeholder" />
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <span class="form-group-label">Radio Label (<code>.form-group-label</code>)</legend>
            <div class="radio">
              <label class="form-label">
                <input type="radio" name="styleguide-radio" />
                Option one
              </label>
            </div>

            <div class="radio">
              <label class="form-label">
                <input type="radio" name="styleguide-radio" />
                Option two
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <span class="form-group-label">Checkbox Label (<code>.form-group-label</code>)</legend>

            <div class="checkbox">
              <label class="form-label">
                <input type="checkbox" />
                Option one
              </label>
            </div>

            <div class="checkbox">
              <label class="form-label">
                <input type="checkbox" />
                Option two
              </label>
            </div>
          </div>

        </form>
      </div>


      <h2 id="styleguide-alerts">Alerts</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/modules/alert.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/modules/alert.css.scss</a>
      <p>Alerts are used for system messages to the user.</p>

      <div class="example">
        <p>
          <div class="alert alert-info alert-dismissable">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            This is a <strong>info alert</strong>.
          </div>
        </p>

        <p>
          <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissable">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            This is a <strong>success alert</strong>.
          </div>
        </p>

        <p>
          <div class="alert alert-error alert-dismissable">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            This is a <strong>error alert</strong>.
          </div>
        </p>
      </div>


      <h2 id="styleguide-panels">Panels</h2>
      <a href="https://github.com/asm-helpful/helpful-web/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/modules/panel.css.scss">app/assets/stylesheets/modules/panel.css.scss</a>
      <p>Panels are used for short forms in their own box. They use 50% of available width, with a limit on 500px.</p>
      <p>
        Panels can also be used as models by adding the class <code>.panel-fixed</code>. If you want to mute the background, you can add an empty div with class <code>.panel-overlay</code>.
      </p>

      <div class="example">
        <div class="panel-outside">
          If you want to align text with the insides of a panel, you can by adding <code>.panel-outside</code> to the text you want to align.
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>This is a basic panel.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>Main panel content goes in <code>.panel-body</code></p>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-footer">
            <p>and an optional <code>.panel-footer</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
